reviews.title: Great!
reviews.text:
A successful first evening in Harlingen ends with good beer/cyclist and delicious hot dog/burger. 
The team was super nice and friendly, the atmosphere relaxed, we felt very comfortable and will come back .

reviews.title: A perfect mix of industry and grandma's living room⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️
reviews.text:
Beautiful brewery with great views!
Located directly on the docks, there are a variety of homemade beers here. There are typical Dutch snacks, burgers and hot dogs. On request some dishes were explained to us in English.
Super cute furnishings and the various furniture invite you to sit together comfortably🥰🥰.
The staff were all very friendly and accommodating. 
The restaurant and toilets are clean.🥰

reviews.title: Nice tasting room found by chance.
reviews.text:
Nice place where we came across by chance.
We enjoyed a delicious and well-stocked drinks board, service is friendly which also advised for a Weizen. And that fitted very well! There is also a small play area for children. Picked some beers to take home at checkout 

If we are in the area again we definitely come here again and definitely recommend it!

reviews.title: At the port
reviews.text: During the fishing days I end up here to do a beer.  What a cool location this brewery has. Outside on the quay some beers done. You can only order if you are sitting at a table! Inside the clapper are 3 cards. Would rather see the assortment on 1 menu. Too bad we were told too late that they also have beers next to the menu. What was also striking was that not all staff were wearing company clothes. Before checkout but someone wanted with mobile ATM on him.

tips.body: Vraag om de bieren naast de kaart

reviews.title: Great spot for a coffee break
reviews.text: We were passing Harlingen on the motorway system, but rather than using a mundane service station for a coffee break we decided to chance our arm and drive into the town to find somewhere more personal. Well, we hit the jackpot with this excellent cafe/restaurant, located alongside the quay in the harbour. We were greeted at the door by the owner’s friendly dog who presented us with a beer mat in the hope that we would play with him. He was in luck! We had excellent coffee and biscuits sitting on some comfortable settees overlooking the harbour where there was plenty of boating activity to view. Whilst we did not stop for a meal the staff and location were excellent. There is also a micro brewery on the premises, so ideal for beer drinkers too.

tips.body: We did not stop for food

reviews.title: nice place to have a drink
reviews.text:
sat on the terrace with a beer and delicious (beer) bitterballen
friendly service
nice view, especially from the 1st floor

reviews.title: New place
reviews.text: After a great day to Vlieland we had a beer at this new place. Although it is still under construction, we enjoyed a “Slim Simmer” and “Wad Weizen”. Two great tasting beers! Had a lovely chat to the owners. They obviously know their craft and are very passionate. If you appreciate a boutique beer with a great story and nice views, this place is a must.

reviews.title: Not easy to find but give it a try
reviews.text:
This relaxed and easy going cafe/lounge bar is located at the boulevard behind the seawall near the railway station. 
There are two large barracks. The one on the left houses the 'BrouwDok'. They sell Harlingen-brew beer. Music and ambiance are great. 
I think a hidden gem. 

In the other barrack by the way is a skeleton of a cachalot ('potvis' in Dutch) and right next to it they build a replica of the explorer Willem Barentsz used in 1594.
